obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47592)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and duration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47592&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may he called the ^1[Coffee Act], 1942.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*].`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Coffee Market Expansion Act" (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch., for "expect Part B States".`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 4 of 1947, s. 2.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47593)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of Union control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 4, for s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47593&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[2. Declaration as to expediency of Union control.--It is hereby declared that it is`
  line `expedient in the public interest that the Union should take under its control the coffee industry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47594)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47594&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `(a) "the Board" means the ^1[`
  line `^2* * * Coffee Board] constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `^3[(aa) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Board;]`
  line
  line `(b) "coffee" means the commodity derived from the fruit of the rubiaceous plant known`
  line `by that name, and includes raw coffee, cured coffee, uncured coffee, roasted coffee and`
  line `prepared coffee;`
  line
  line `^4[(c) "Commissioner", means a Commissioner of Customs as specified in clause (b) of section 3`
  line `of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(d) "curing" means the application to raw coffee of mechanical processes other than pulping for`
  line `the purpose of preparing it for marketing;`
  line
  line `(e) "curing establishment" means any place to which raw coffee is sent by a registered owner for`
  line `curing, and includes any estate which the Board may declare to be a curing establishment for the`
  line `purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `^5[(ee) "dealer" means a person carrying on the business of selling coffee, whether wholesale or by`
  line retail;]
  line
  line `(f) "estate" means an area administered as one unit which contains land planted with`
  line `coffee plants;`
  line
  line `^6[(ff) "India" means the territory of India excluding the State of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir*;]
  line
  line `(g) "Indian Coffee Cess Committee" means the Indian Coffee Cess Committee constituted under the Indian Coffee Cess Act, 1935 (14 of 1935);`
  line
  line `^7[(h) "free sale quota" means that portion, stated in terms of bulk or weight, of the`
  line `whole of the coffee produced by the estate in the year, which a registered estate is`
  line `permitted under this Act to sell;]`
  line
  line `^8[(i) "owner", in relation to any land planted with coffee plants, includes,--`
  line
  line `(1) any agent of the owner, and`
  line
  line `(2) a mortgagee, lessee or other person in actual possession of the land;]`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "registered estate" means an estate in respect of which an owner is registered under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14, and includes also any estate in respect of which an owner is`
  line `required to be registered under the provisions of that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(l) "registered owner" means an owner of a registered estate who has been or is`
  line `required to be registered under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
  line
  line `(m) "surplus pool" means the stock of coffee accumulated by the Board out of the amounts`
  line `delivered to the Board under section 25;`
  line
  line `^10[(n) "year" means the period of twelve months beginning with the first day of July and ending`
  line `with the thirtieth day of June next following.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 2, for "India Coffee Market Expansion Board".`
  line
  line `2. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 50 of 1954, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 85, for cl. (c).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 2 of 1944, s. 2.`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 2, for cl. (h) (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 2, for cl. (i) (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `9. Cl. (ll) Omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule which was ins. by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 2, for cl. (n) (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `*.Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47595)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47595&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board constituted by the name of the Indian`
  line `Coffee Market Expansion Board under section 4 of the Indian Coffee Market Expansion`
  line `Ordinance, 1940 (13 of 1940), shall be the ^1[Coffee Board] for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[^3[^4(2) The Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(b) three Members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of`
  line `the People and one by the Council of States; and`
  line
  line `(c) such number of other members not exceeding twenty-nine as the Central`
  line `Government may think expedient, to be appointed by that Government by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette from among persons who are in its opinion capable of`
  line representing,--
  line
  line `(i) Governments of the principal coffee-growing States;`
  line
  line `(ii) coffee-growing industry;`
  line
  line `(iii) coffee trade interests;`
  line
  line `(iv) curing establishments;`
  line
  line `(v) interests of labour;`
  line
  line `(vi) interests of consumers; and`
  line
  line `(vii) such other interests as, in the opinion of the Central Government, ought to be`
  line `represented on the Board.`
  line
  line `(2A) The number of persons to be appointed as members from each of the categories specified in`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2), the term of office of, the procedure to be followed in the discharge of`
  line `their functions by, and the manner of filling vacancies among, the members of the Board shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2B) Any officer of the Central Government when deputed by that Government in this behalf`
  line `shall have the right to attend meetings of the Board and take part in the proceedings thereof but`
  line `shall not be entitled to vote.]`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *]`
  line
  line `^6[(4)] No act done by the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board.`
  line
  line `^7[(5) It is hereby declared that the office of member of the Board shall not disqualify its`
  line `holder for being chosen as, or for being, a member of either House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 6, for "Indian Coffee Board" (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-sections (2) and (3) ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 3, for sub-section (2) and (2A) (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-section (3) which was ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 3, omitted by Act 48 of 1961, s. 3 (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `6. The original sub-section (2) renumbered as sub-section (4) by Act 7 of 1943, s. 3.`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47596)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Incorporation of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47596&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall be a body corporate by the name of the`
  line `^1[^2* * * Coffee Board], having perpetual succession and a common seal, with power to acquire and`
  line `hold property, both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall by the said name sue and be`
  line sued.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 4, for "Indian Coffee Market Expansion Board".`
  line
  line `2. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 50 of 1954, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47597)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vesting of property in the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47597&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `So long as this Act remains in force all property, movable or immovable, of or belonging to the Indian Coffee Cess Committee shall vest in the Board and`
  line `all debts and liabilities of the said Committee shall be transferred to the Board, and the officers and`
  line `servants of the said Committee shall be officers and servants on the staff of the Board and the said`
  line `Committee shall be suspended.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (47598)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Consultation with the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47598&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Consultation with the Board.--Before taking any action touching the affairs of the Board`
  line `under this Act, the Central Government shall ordinarily consult the Board :`
  line
  line `Provided that no action taken by the Central Government shall be invalid or called in question merely`
  line `on the ground that the action was taken without such consultation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47599)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees, staff and agents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (1) omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47599&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may appoint such committees for such purposes and may employ such staff as it thinks`
  line `necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may authorise agents to discharge on its behalf its functions in relation to the`
  line `marketing, storing and curing of coffee.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47600)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Salary and allowances of Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 10, for ss. 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47600&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Salary and allowances of Chairman.--The Chairman shall be entitled to such salary and`
  line `allowances and such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters`
  line `as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (47601)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title Vice-Chairman.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 10, for ss. 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47601&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Vice-Chairman.--The Board shall elect from amongst its members a Vice-Chairman who shall`
  line `exercise such of the powers and perform such of the duties of the Chairman as may be prescribed or as`
  line `may be delegated to him by the Chairman.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (47602)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Chief Coffee Marketing Officer, Secretary and other Staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 10, for ss. 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47602&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Chief Coffee Marketing Officer, Secretary and other staff.--(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall appoint an officer to be called the Chief Coffee Marketing Officer and a Secretary to the Board`
  line `and may appoint a Deputy Secretary to the Board and such number of Marketing Officers as may be`
  line `necessary, to exercise such powers and to perform such duties under the direction of the Board as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers appointed under this section shall be entitled to such salaries and allowances`
  line `and such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as`
  line `may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (47603)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Dissolution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47603&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When the Board is dissolved by reason of this Act having`
  line `ceased to be in force, the unexpended balance of all money received by the Board under the`
  line `Coffee Market Expansion Ordinance, 1940 (13 of 1940), or under this Act except money in the`
  line `pool fund, shall be disposed of in such manner as the Central Government may direct. The Central`
  line `Government shall disburse the money in the pool fund in the same manner as the Board would`
  line `have done had it continued to exist.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
