obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (47607)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Registration of owners of coffee estates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47607&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every owner of land planted with`
  line `coffee plants, whether such land is comprised in one estate or in more than one estate and`
  line `whether it is situated wholly or only partly in India, shall, before the expiration of one month`
  line `from the date on which he first became owner of such estate or estates, apply to the registering`
  line `officer appointed in this behalf by the State Government to be registered as an owner in respect`
  line `of each estate owned by him, and any registration made before the commencement of the`
  line `Coffee (Amendment) Act, 1961 (48 of 1961) shall be deemed to have been made under this`
  line sub-section.]
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) A registration once made shall continue in force until it is cancelled by the`
  line `registering officer.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 6, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (4) omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (47608)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47608&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules to carry into effect the provisions of section 14.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may prescribe`
  line `the form of the application for registration and for cancellation of registration, the fee payable`
  line `on such applications, the particulars to be included in such applications, the procedure to be`
  line `followed in granting and cancelling registration, the registers to be kept by registering officers,`
  line `and the supply by registering officers of information to the Board.-`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (47609)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Fixation of prices for sale of coffee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47609&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `4^1[16. Fixation of prices for sale of coffee.--(1) The Central Government may ^2`
  line `* * * by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette fix the price or prices at which coffee may be sold wholesale`
  line `or retail in the Indian market.`
  line
  line `(2) No registered owner or licensed curer or dealer shall sell coffee wholesale or retail in`
  line `the Indian market at a price or prices higher than the price or prices fixed under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 5, for s. 16.`
  line
  line `2. The words "after consultation with the Board" omitted by Act 50 of 1954, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (47610)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Sale of coffee in excess of free sale quota.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 5, for s. 17 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47610&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Sale of coffee in excess of free sale quotas.--No registered owner shall sell or`
  line `contract to sell coffee from any registered estate if by such sale the free sale quota allotted to`
  line `that estate is exceeded nor shall a registered owner sell or contract to sell any coffee produced`
  line `on his estate in any year for which no free sale quota is allotted to the estate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (47611)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Sale of coffee, how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47611&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No registered owner shall sell coffee unless either--`
  line
  line `(a) it has been cured at or is delivered to the buyer through a curing establishment licensed under`
  line `section 28, or`
  line
  line `(b) it is sold under and in accordance with the provisions of a licence procured from the Board`
  line `under section 24.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (47612)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47612&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `[Storage or sale of coffee on or from unregistered estate.] Rep. by the Coffee (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1961 (48 of 1961), s. 8 (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (47613)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Export of coffee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47613&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No coffee shall be exported from ^1[India] otherwise than by the`
  line `Board or under an authorisation granted by the Board in the prescribed manner and in the prescribed cases, and the provisions of the ^2[Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), shall have effect as if`
  line `the provision made by this section had been made by notification issued under section 11] of`
  line `that Act:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that nothing herein contained shall apply to coffee--`
  line
  line `(i) shipped as stores on board any vessel or aircraft in such quantity as the`
  line `^4[Commissioner] considers reasonable, having regard to the number of the crew and`
  line `passengers and the length of the voyage or journey, as the case may be, on which the vessel`
  line `or aircraft is about to proceed, or`
  line
  line `^5[(ii) carried as personal baggage of a passenger, not exceeding such quantities as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, or`
  line
  line `(iii) exported for such purposes and in such quantities as the Central Government may specify in`
  line `the like manner :]]`
  line
  line `^6[Provided further that the Central Government may, by order in writing, specify the quantity of coffee which shall be permitted for export during any year and where any such order is`
  line `made, no coffee shall be exported from India in excess of the said quantity :]`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may exempt from the operation of this`
  line `section, either absolutely or subject to conditions, the export of coffee from ^1[India] ^7[to the`
  line `State of Jammu and Kashmir*] or to any foreign settlement bounded by India.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "the States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994. s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 16, for the first proviso (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 85, for "Collector".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 9, for cls. (ii), (iii) and (iv) (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `6. The Proviso ins. by Act 50 of 1954, s.16 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 3 and Sch., ibid., for "to a Part B State".`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (47614)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Re-import of coffee exported from India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47614&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) No coffee which has been exported from`
  line `India shall be re-imported into ^1[India] except under and in accordance with permit granted by the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The Board may in any fit case grant such a permit and no charge shall be made`
  line therefor.
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (47615)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Free sale quota.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 7, for s. 22 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47615&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Free sale quota.--(1) Unless with the previous sanction of the Central Government`
  line `the Board decides that no free sale quotas shall be allotted, the Board shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, allot to each registered estate a free sale quota for the year.`
  line
  line `(2) The free sale quota shall be a fixed percentage, common to all registered estates, not`
  line `exceeding fifty per cent. of the probable total production of the estate in the year as estimated by`
  line `the Board :`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government, allot`
  line `such quota at a percentage higher than fifty per cent. of the said probable total production.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may at any time vary the free sale quota by varying the fixed percentage`
  line `common to all registered estates, or may express the whole or any part of the free sale quota of`
  line `an estate in terms of bulk instead of in terms of weight.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (47616)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Returns to be made by registered owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47616&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered owner shall furnish to the`
  line `Board at the prescribed times and in the prescribed manner such returns as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If any registered owner fails to furnish the returns required under sub-section (1) in respect of any estate, the Board may ^1[without prejudice to any penalty to which the said owner is`
  line `liable under section 37A] refuse to allot ^2[a free sale quota] to that estate, or, where ^2[a free sale`
  line `quota] has already been allotted, may cancel it.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may authorise an officer to visit any estate at any time to verify the accuracy`
  line `of any return made under this section or to ascertain the productive capacity of the estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 8.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 8, for "an internal sale quota" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (47617)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Licences for sale of uncured coffee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "internal sale quota" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47617&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The registered owner of any estate may, subject to`
  line `the prescribed conditions and so long as the ^1[free sale quota] allotted to that estate will not be`
  line `exceeded by the proposed sale, obtain from the Board a licence for the sale from that estate of`
  line `uncured coffee.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (47618)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Surplus coffee and surplus pool.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47618&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) All coffee produced by a registered estate in excess`
  line `of the amount specified in the ^1[free sale quota] allotted to that estate ^2[or when no ^3[free sale`
  line `quota] have been allotted to estates, all coffee produced by the estate], shall be delivered to the`
  line `Board for inclusion in the surplus pool by the owner of the estate or by the curing establishment`
  line `receiving the coffee from the estate:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that where no ^3[free sale quotas] have been allotted to estates, the Chairman may`
  line `allow the owner of any estate to retain with himself for purposes of consumption by his family`
  line `and for purposes of seed, such quantity of coffee as the Chairman may think reasonable :`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Central Government is satisfied that it is not practicable for`
  line `any class of owners producing coffee in any specified area to comply with the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section on account of the small quantity of coffee produced by them or on account of their`
  line `estates being situated in a remote locality, the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, exempt such class of owners from the provisions of this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `(2) Delivery shall be made to the Board in such places, ^5[at such times] and in such manner`
  line `as the Board may direct, and such directions may provide for partial delivery to the surplus`
  line `pool at any time whether or not at that time the ^1[free sale quota] has been exceeded; and the`
  line `coffee delivered shall be such as to represent fairly in kind and quality the produce of the`
  line `estate. The Board may reject any consignment offered for delivery which does not satisfy this`
  line `requirement, but shall not reject any consignment merely for a defect in curing.`
  line
  line `(3) Coffee delivered for inclusion in the surplus pool shall upon delivery to the Board`
  line `remain under the control of the Board which shall be responsible for storage, curing where`
  line `necessary, and marketing of the coffee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall ^6* * * ^7[from time to time] prepare a differential scale for the valuation of coffee, and shall in accordance with that scale classify the coffee in each consignment`
  line `delivered for inclusion in the surplus pool according to its kind and quality, and shall make an`
  line `assessment of its value based on its quantity, kind and quality.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may with the consent of a registered owner, ^8* * * treat as having been`
  line `delivered for inclusion in the surplus pool any coffee from such estate which the registered`
  line `owner may agree to have so treated.`
  line
  line `(6) When coffee has been delivered or is treated as having been delivered for inclusion in the`
  line `surplus pool, the registered owner whose coffee has been so delivered or is treated as having`
  line `been so delivered shall retain no rights in respect of such coffee except his right to receive the`
  line `payments referred to in section 34.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by s. 10, ibid., "for internal sale quota" (14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 10.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "internal sale quota" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Added by Act 50 of 1954, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 10.`
  line
  line `6. The words "with the concurrence of the Chief Coffee Marketing Officer" omitted by Act 50 of 1954, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 10.`
  line
  line `8. The words "before an internal sale quota has been allotted to an estate" omitted by Act 7 of 1943, s. 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (47619)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Sales of coffee by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47619&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall take all practical measures to market`
  line `the coffee included in the surplus pool, and all sales thereof shall be conducted by or through the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The Board may purchase for inclusion in the surplus pool coffee not delivered for inclusion in it.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (47620)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Coffee to be cured in licensed curing establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47620&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No registered owner shall cause or`
  line `allow coffee to be cured elsewhere than in a licensed curing establishment, whether the curing`
  line `establishment is maintained by himself or by another person.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (47621)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Licensing of curing establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47621&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Every establishment for curing coffee shall obtain from`
  line `the Board a licence to operate as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (47622)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Information to be supplied to the Board in connection with curing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47622&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered`
  line `owner when sending coffee to a curing establishment shall report to the Board, separately for`
  line `each estate from which coffee is sent, the amount of coffee sent; and the curing establishment`
  line `shall, in accordance with such instructions as may be issued by the Board and having regard to`
  line `the ^1[free sale quota] of the estate ^2[where one has been allotted], apportion each such consignment into two parts, one part consisting of coffee intended ^3[for free sale] and one part of coffee`
  line `intended to be delivered for inclusion in the surplus pool and shall report to the Board the`
  line `amount of coffee in each such part ^2[Where no ^4[free sale quotas] have been allotted to estates,`
  line `the curing establishment shall report merely the whole amount of coffee sent in each such`
  line consignment.]
  line
  line `(2) A registered owner curing coffee in a curing establishment maintained by himself shall`
  line `supply to the Board the information specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) A curing establishment which buys or receives uncured coffee from any person shall`
  line `ascertain the estate on which the coffee was produced and shall report to the Board the quantity`
  line `of coffee so obtained and the estate or estates from which it came.`
  line
  line `(4) Every curing establishment shall maintain accounts in such forms as may be required by the Board and such accounts shall be open to inspection at any time by the Board or by an officer authorised in this behalf by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 11, for "internal sale quota" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 11.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 11 for "internal sale" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., "internal sale quotas" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (47623)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Separate funds to be maintained by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47623&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall maintain two separate funds,`
  line `a general fund and a pool fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (47624)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `General fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47624&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. General fund.--(1) To the general fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all amounts paid to the Board by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) any sums transferred to the general fund under the proviso to sub-section (2) of ^2[section 32;`
  line and]
  line
  line `^3[(c) all fees levied and collected by the Board under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) The general fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) to meet the expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) to meet the cost of such measures as the Board may consider advisable to undertake`
  line `for promoting agricultural and technological research in the interest of the coffee industry in`
  line India;
  line
  line `(c) for making such grants to coffee estates or for meeting the cost of such other`
  line `assistance to coffee estates as the Board may think necessary for the development of`
  line `such estates;`
  line
  line `(d) to meet the cost of such measures as the Board considers advisable to undertake for`
  line `promoting the sale and increasing the consumption in India and elsewhere of coffee produced in India; and`
  line
  line `(e) to meet the expenses for securing better working conditions and the provision and`
  line `improvement of amenities and incentives for workers.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 18, for s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 10, for "section 32" (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (47625)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Pool fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47625&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) To the pool fund shall be credited all sums realised by sales by the Board of`
  line `Coffee from the surplus pool.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^1[The pool fund] shall be applied only to--`
  line
  line `(a) the making to registered owners of estates of payments proportionate to the value of the`
  line `coffee delivered by them for inclusion in the surplus pool;`
  line
  line `(b) the costs of storing, curing and marketing coffee deposited in and of administering the surplus`
  line `pool ;`
  line
  line `(c) the purchase of coffee not delivered for inclusion in the surplus pool:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where, after the requirements of the, clauses of this sub-section have been`
  line `met, there remains any excess in the pool fund, the Board may, with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, transfer the whole or any part of such excess to the credit of the general`
  line fund.]
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 12, for certain words. (w.e.f 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 16 of 1944, s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (47626)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of the Board to make donation to the Gandhi National Memorial Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 34 of 1949, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47626&sectionno=32A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Power of the Board to make donation to the Gandhi National Memorial`
  line `Fund.--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 32, the Board may apply any part of`
  line `the pool fund to the making of a donation to the Fund known as the Gandhi National`
  line `Memorial Fund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (47627)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to borrow.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47627&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, subject to any prescribed conditions, borrow on the`
  line `security of the general fund or the pool fund for any purposes for which it is authorised to`
  line `expend money from such fund, or on the security of the coffee delivered or treated as delivered`
  line `for inclusion in the surplus pool for any purposes for which it is authorised to expend money`
  line `from the pool fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (47628)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 37
  title `Payments to registered owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1 Added by Act 7 of 1943, s. 12.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47628&sectionno=34&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall at such times as it thinks fit make to`
  line `registered owners who have delivered coffee for inclusion in the surplus pool such payments out of the`
  line `pool fund as it may think proper.`
  line
  line `(2) The sum of all payments made under sub-section (1) to any one registered owner shall`
  line `bear to the sum of the payments made to all registered owners the same proportion as the value`
  line `of the coffee delivered by him out of the year's crop to the surplus pool bears to the value of all`
  line `coffee delivered to the surplus pool out of that year's crop:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that in calculating the sum of all payments made under sub-section (1) and the`
  line `value of the coffee delivered to the surplus pool out of the years crop, respectively, any payment`
  line `accepted by a registered owner as final payment in immediate settlement for coffee delivered by`
  line `him for inclusion in the surplus pool and the value of any such coffee shall be excluded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (47629)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Failure to register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47629&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Any owner of a coffee estate who fails to apply for registration in`
  line `accordance with section 14 shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line `rupees and to a further fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for each month after the`
  line `first during which such failure continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (47630)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Contraventions of sections 16, 17 and 18.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47630&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any registered owner who contravenes`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 16, or section 17 or section 18, any licensed curer`
  line `^1[or dealer] who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 16, ^2* * * shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) When a registered owner is convicted under this section, the Board may thereafter`
  line `deduct from any payment to be made under section 34 to such registered owner a sum equal`
  line `to the value as estimated by the Board of any coffee unlawfully sold by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 2 of 1944, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 48 of 1961, s. 11 (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (47631)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Unlicensed curing establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47631&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If any curing establishment operates as such without a`
  line `licence, the owner shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (47632)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 41
  title `Contravention of section 23(1).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 13.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47632&sectionno=37A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[37A. Contravention of section 23 (1). --Any registered owner who fails to furnish the return`
  line `required by sub-section (1) of section 23 as required by that sub-section shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (47633)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 42
  title `False returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47633&sectionno=38&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Any person who makes in any return to be furnished under section 23 or`
  line `in any report to be made under section 29 any statement which is false and which he knows to be`
  line `false or does not believe to be true shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (47634)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 43
  title `Contravention of section 25.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 14.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47634&sectionno=38A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Contravention of section 25.--Any registered owner or licensed curer who fails to`
  line `deliver any coffee to the Board as required by or under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 25`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, and the Court by which`
  line `such person is convicted may order the confiscation and delivery to the Board of any coffee in`
  line `respect of which the offence was committed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_b:
  sectionId (47635)
  sectionNo 38B
  orderNo 44
  title `Powers to seize coffee withheld from inclusion in surplus pool.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 14.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47635&sectionno=38B&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[38B. Powers to seize coffee withheld from inclusion in surplus pool.-- If the Board is satisfied`
  line `that any coffee which is required under the provisions of section 25 to be delivered for inclusion in`
  line `the surplus pool is being or is likely to be disposed of otherwise than by such delivery, the Board`
  line `may order the seizure of such coffee, and may authorise an officer of the Board to effect seizure`
  line `thereof for delivery for inclusion in the surplus pool, and such authorisation shall be sufficient`
  line `warrant for such officer to take all steps necessary to secure possession of the coffee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (47636)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 45
  title Obstruction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47636&sectionno=39&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Whoever obstructs any member or officer of the Board or any person`
  line `authorised by the Board or by the Central Government in the discharge of any duty imposed on`
  line `or entrusted to him under this Act, or who having control over or custody of any records fails to`
  line `produce such records when required to do so or refuses information lawfully asked for by a`
  line `member or officer of the Board by a person authorised by the Board or by the Central Government to`
  line `inspect such records or ask for such information shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39_a:
  sectionId (47637)
  sectionNo 39A
  orderNo 46
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47637&sectionno=39A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[39A. Offences by companies.--(1) If the person committing any offence under this Act is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his`
  line `knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where an offence under this Act`
  line `has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with`
  line `the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director,`
  line `manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (47638)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 47
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47638&sectionno=40&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court other than the Court of ^1[a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class] shall take cognizance of any offence punishable`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under section 35 except on`
  line `complaint made by an officer authorised in this behalf by the State Government ^2[or of the`
  line `offence specified in sub-section (2) of section 16 except on complaint made by an officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf either by the State Government or by the Board] or of an offence`
  line `punishable under any other section except on complaint made with the previous sanction of`
  line `the Central Government by an officer authorised in this behalf by the Board:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the`
  line `previous sanction of the Central Government shall not be necessary for complaints in such cases or`
  line `classes of cases as may be specified in the notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 13, for "a Magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 1944, s. 4.`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 7 of 1943, s. 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (47639)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 48
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47639&sectionno=41&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `[Power of board to determine amount of coffee sold by an estate.] Rep. by the Coffee`
  line `(Amendment Act, 1961 (48 of 1961), s. 12 (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (47640)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 49
  title `Control by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47640&sectionno=42&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) All acts of the Board shall be subject to the control`
  line `of the Central Government which may cancel, suspend or modify as it thinks fit any action taken by the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The records of the Board shall be open to inspection at all reasonable times by any officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (47641)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 50
  title `Appeals to the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47641&sectionno=43&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the`
  line `Board refusing a licence to or cancelling the licence of a curing establishment may, within`
  line `sixty days of the making of the order, appeal to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person making an appeal under this section shall pay a fee of five rupees which`
  line `shall be credited to Central Revenues.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (47642)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 51
  title `Inspection of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47642&sectionno=44&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[Any Person authorised in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government or by the Board or any Member of the Board so authorised by the Chairman in`
  line `writing or any officer of the Board, may enter at all reasonable times] any estate or any`
  line `curing establishment ^2[or any place where coffee is stored or exposed for sale,] and may`
  line `require the production for his inspection of any records kept therein, or ask for any`
  line `information relating to the production, storage or sale of coffee ^3***.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 20, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 16.`
  line
  line `3. The words "by the estate" omitted by s. 16, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (47643)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 52
  title `Accounts of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47643&sectionno=45&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall keep accounts in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed of all money received and expended by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts shall be kept separately for the general fund and the pool fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall cause the accounts to be audited annually by auditors appointed by`
  line `the Central Government, and the auditors shall have power to disallow any item of`
  line `expenditure which has, in their opinion, been incurred otherwise than in accordance with this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may on the application of the Board allow any item of`
  line `expenditure disallowed by the auditors under sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (47644)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 53
  title `Inspection of records of the Board and obtaining of copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. The words "to whom an internal sale quota is allotted" omitted by Act 7 of 1943, s. 17.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47644&sectionno=46&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any registered`
  line `owner ^1*** may, subject to the prescribed conditions, inspect the records maintained by the`
  line `Board and may on Payment of the prescribed fee obtain copies of any proceedings or orders`
  line `of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (47645)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 54
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47645&sectionno=47&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `All Contracts for the sale of coffee in so far as they are at variance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act shall be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to contracts to which under`
  line `section 47 of the Coffee Market Expansion Ordinance, 1940 (13 of 1940), that Ordinance did`
  line `not apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47_a:
  sectionId (47646)
  sectionNo 47A
  orderNo 55
  title `Bar of legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 1943, s. 18.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47646&sectionno=47A&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[47A. Bar of legal proceedings.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Board or any officer of the Board for or in respect of anything in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (47647)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of the Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094&sectionId=47647&sectionno=48&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00012_194207_1523353762094
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules may be made providing for all`
  line `or any of the following matters : --`
  line
  line `^2[(i) the constitution of the Board, the number of persons to be appointed as members`
  line `from each of the categories specified in clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 4, the term`
  line `of office and other conditions of service of, the procedure to be followed by, and the manner`
  line `of filling vacancies among, the members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) the circumstances in which, and the authority by which, members may be`
  line removed;]
  line
  line `(iii) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the Board and at committees`
  line `thereof for the conduct of business and the number of members which shall form a`
  line `quorum at a meeting ;`
  line
  line `(iv) the maintenance by the Board of records of business transacted by the Board and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof to the Central Government ;`
  line
  line `(v) the holding of a minimum number of meetings of the Board every year ;`
  line
  line `(vi) the powers of the Board, its Chairman and committees thereof with respect to the incurring of`
  line `expenditure ;`
  line
  line `(vii) the conditions subject to which the Board may incur expenditure outside India ;`
  line
  line `(viii) the preparation of budget estimates of receipts and expenditure of the Board and the`
  line `authority by which the estimates are to be sanctioned ;`
  line
  line `(ix) the maintenance of the accounts of income and expenditure of the Board and the audit of such`
  line accounts;
  line
  line `(x) the deposit of the funds of the Board in banks and the investment of such funds ;`
  line
  line `(xi) the re-appropriation of the estimated savings from any budget head to any other budget head;`
  line
  line `(xii) the conditions subject to which the Board may borrow funds ;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the conditions subject to which and the manner in which contracts may be`
  line `entered into by or on behalf of the Board ;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the delegation to the committee or Chairman or Vice-Chairman or members or`
  line `officers of the Board of any of the powers and duties of the Board under this Act ;`
  line
  line `(xv) the staff which may be employed by the Board and the pay and allowances and`
  line `leave and other conditions of service of officers (other than those appointed by the Central`
  line `Government) and other employees of the Board ;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the travelling and other allowances of members of the Board and of committees`
  line `thereof ;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the maintenance of the registers and other records of the Board and its various`
  line `committees ;`
  line
  line `(xviii) the manner in which the ^3[free sale quota] of coffee estates shall be`
  line `determined ;`
  line
  line `(xix) the manner in which the Board shall exercise its powers of buying and selling`
  line `coffee ;`
  line
  line `(xx) the appointment by the Board of agents ;`
  line
  line `(xxi) the conditions to be fulfilled by a curing establishment before a licence to operate as such`
  line `can be issued ;`
  line
  line `(xxii) the form of, and the particulars to be contained in, any returns or reports to be made to the`
  line `Board under this Act ;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) the form of, manner of application for, fees payable for, procedure in granting`
  line `and conditions governing, the licences and permits to be issued by the Board ;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of coffee or any product of`
  line `coffee ;`
  line
  line `(xxv) any other matter (other than any matter specified in section 15) which is to be or may be`
  line `prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament,, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry`
  line `of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should`
  line `not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect,`
  line `as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1954, s. 21, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 48 of 1961, s. 13, for cls. (i) and (ii) (w.e.f. 19-4-1962).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 14, for "internal sale quota" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 48 of 1985, s. 5, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
